latestIgtvVideos.title: One whole year.
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
There’s not a day that goes by that doesn’t leave me asking myself a ton of questions. Wondering how we could have helped more. Feeling a heavy spirit of defeat knowing his life ended the way it did. Tears of sadness because we lost it. Tears of joy because we lived it. Rejoicing for the new life of our little girl, yet lamenting the tragic loss to suicide. One life beginning, another life ending. It’s all a lot. It’s still a lot. It’s changed me. My perception, my attitude, my perspective. My dad wasn’t a perfect dad by any means. In fact, there were a lot of silent years as a kid where I was left in the same spot I am now— asking myself a ton of questions. Wondering. Questioning. But he was my dad. The most beautiful part to the story was the reconnecting part. The part that very much felt like a new life and another chance to get this relationship right. Though we were just getting started, I’m forever grateful we began again.
I’m committed now more than ever to shut the door on generational footholds. There’s not a day that goes by where I don’t wake up with the Holy Spirit reminding me He’s placed me here for such a time as this. To rewrite history. To change the narrative. To declare victory over generational depression and alcoholism. The buck stops with me. My husband deserves it, my baby girl deserves it, my legacy deserves it. I watched my dad cheer me on in this. He knew I was on mission. 
I’ve said it before and I’ll say it again, if you’re waiting to press restart on a relationship— do it. Forgive them. Love them. Show up for them. Push all of your pride and anger and questions to the side and just show up. Begin again. I’m grateful I did. 
Missing you extra this week, dad. Can’t believe it’s already been a year without you.

latestPosts.caption:
One camera. One city. One rockstar.
And somehow I got the invite to be in the room for all of it. 🎤📸

This week, @todayshow brought me back out — this time to capture @machinegunkelly lighting up Rockefeller Plaza in the heart of NYC. First time in the city. First time VIP. First time shooting a live show like this… and man, I’m still buzzing.

All frames shot straight out of camera — no edits, just vibes and film simulations I couldn’t wait to unload back at the hotel.

If there’s one thing I learned about MGK, he shows up for the fans.

Big stage energy, bigger heart. Dude throws down like a rock legend but loves like a hometown hero.

Drop your favorite MGK song in the comments ⬇️🎶

 @carsondaly @craigmelvinnbc @savannahguthrie @jennabhager @angielassman @alroker @kevinschatell @dylandreyernbc
